            <title>[SOLR-4314] Lucene doc link in example&apos;s solrconfig.xml is dead after Lucene javadoc reorganization</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-4314</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Example&apos;s solrconfig.xml points to lucene 3.5 documentation for IndexDeletionPolicy javadoc.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The link is dead (possibly in other places too).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The fix is here: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/lucene-solr/pull/6/files#diff-0&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/lucene-solr/pull/6/files#diff-0&lt;/a&gt; , just one line copy/paste. Though, that&apos;s lucene 4.0 link, I am not sure if there is a different one for Lucene 4.1 (catch-22...).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
